## Working from intent

- **Bootstrap.** If `.doctrina/intake.md` exists with `Status: pending`,
  the specs have not been written yet. Before anything else, run
  `doctrina intake` and execute the printed bootstrap playbook in one
  linear pass: fill `product.md`, derive capabilities, author one EARS
  spec each, run the quality gates (`doctrina clarify --all`,
  `doctrina validate`), then flip the intake to `Status: converted`. Ask
  the user only when the intake is genuinely ambiguous. After conversion
  the specs are the only source of truth — never edit `intake.md` to
  change requirements.
- **Day-to-day.** Turn a brief request into a scaffolded change with
  `doctrina work "<prompt>"`, then follow the printed work playbook
  (spec delta → tasks → implement → analyze → apply → archive → validate).

